<br>
The larger a sig the longer it takes for anyone to load the page.  If someone has a broken sig, it just takes longer, that is a different issue.<br>
<br>
There are plenty of people who still have to use a modem to play eq, but luckily EQ is designed with that in mind.  I played on a modem for almost the first year of eq, and noticed barely any difference when I got on DSL then on Cable.  The difference is mostly made in your computer hardware.<br>
<br>
So, Size of sigs are still an issue for this board.<br>
<br>
The length and height, keep people from distorting the forums so people who still have their computers set at lower dimensions don't have to scroll back and forth.<br>
<br>
The board looks drab because people's sigs aren't all up and down it?   To me it doesn't look like a flea market anymore.  The truth is, most people don't care what everyone else's sigs look like.  Sigs are for your own personal pleasure.  There might be that 1% of sigs where people actually Go, "COOL SIG", and that can easily be seen the first time in a thread.<br>
<br>
To have to have your sig on every one of your posts is just vain.<br>
<br>
